Project Configuration and Guidelines

Tech Stack:

- React 19 with TypeScript
- Vite as build tool
- TailwindCSS v4 for styling
- React Router v7 for routing
- Vitest & MSW v2 for testing
- React Hook Form + Zod for form management
- shadcn/ui for component library
- Zustand & TanStack Query v5 for state management

Architecture:

- Feature-Sliced Design (FSD) architecture
- App.tsx as the main routing file
- Environment-specific configurations for development and production

Key Focus Areas:

1.  Optimal code splitting and performance optimization for enhanced user experience
2.  Comprehensive testing strategy with latest React testing practices
3.  Version compatibility management for cutting-edge dependencies

Special Instructions for Testing:

- As this project introduces testing for the first time, detailed guidance will be provided
- Focus on current React testing best practices and methodologies
- Step-by-step explanations for test implementation
- Clear examples for different types of tests (unit, integration, e2e)

Version Management:

- Special attention to version compatibility due to usage of latest releases
- Regular version checks and updates for security and feature improvements
- Careful consideration of breaking changes in major version updates

Environment Configuration:

- Separate environment configurations for development and production
- Proper environment variable management
- Environment-specific testing setups

Performance Optimization:

- Implement efficient code splitting strategies
- Optimize bundle size
- Implement lazy loading where appropriate
- Monitor and improve performance metrics
